  "text": "It has previously been demonstrated that lymph nodes undergoing metastatic change experience an increase in blood vessel volume and density prior to experiencing a change in nodal size [CITATION_1] . Ultrasonic color Doppler imaging is able to detect blood flow in and around lymph nodes but is unable to delineate the blood vessels themselves [CITATION_2] .",
